Subject:Re: [Jukebox-list] Bench  testing SHP-1 Amp.
Jim, the amp has nothing to do with the selection process -only the end of =
record or manual reject goes through it.

You should be able to make selections and have the mech stop w/out the amp =
even being connected.

It sounds as though the machine has not had it's electronics rebuilt and th=
e fact that this starts getting worse as it warms up pretty much confirms i=
t.

----Be careful as to the input signal. A "radio" tuner is much higher outpu=
t than a phono pickup and you have no volume control to limit output level.

--I do not recommend testing with a high level source unless you make a pad=
 to reduce it's level. Do you have a phono w/magnetic pickup? That would be=
 ideal here.

These amps are not my favorites, I've seen some really awful meltdowns with=
 scorched boards boards burned through and soot all over the chassis. I hat=
ed working on them and considered it a junk design. They can be civilized, =
but they shouldn't have=A0 been sold without adequate fusing.


At this point, it might be best to pack the electronics up and ship to some=
body with the experience (and patience) to rebuild it.

Rob

