Jim, you go from Pin 6 into 7, Pin 8 into 9.

It doesn't matter if that crosses channels.

As for the ground just connect whatever signal source you are using to chas=
sis ground, or you can Pin 1 on the V.C. plug.

What are you using for a test signal?

BTW: I see that Vern Tisdale has schematics for this amp:

http://www.verntisdale.com/Seeburgschem.htm


Volume pots: http://www.verntisdale.com/schem/shp1-3b.jpg

